Job Description

To enhance our global support team, we are hiring a Technical Support Engineer – L1 with strong and proven customer service experience in the IT market to be based in our Bangalore, India office.

As a Technical Support Engineer – L1, you will build and expand upon our professional excellence in support service to all Kaseya customers, ensuring customer delight by meeting or exceeding internal KPI targets and expectations. With your expertise and passion for problem-solving, you'll play a pivotal role in keeping businesses running smoothly C securely while building lifelong relationships. The successful candidate is expected to maintain a professional, courteous, and customer-first attitude while working on chats, phones C tickets. If you are an overachiever with proven technical support experience who thrives in a fast-paced environment, we want to speak with you.

Required Skills

Excellent knowledge of major operating systems - Windows, macOS C
Familiar with the OSI model C experience troubleshooting Network stack - VLAN, NAT, TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, HTTP/HTTPS using CLI commands (ping, ipconfig, Nmap, traceroute, etc).
Understanding of Encryption - SSL/TLS, Types of Certificates, Encryption
Basic Windows Administration, including Active Directory C Group
Hands-on experience with Patch Management, Application C System performance
Basic system log analysis beyond Event Viewer (e.g., /var/log/, application logs).
Ability to read/write SQL
Experience with Antivirus, Antimalware, Defender, EDR, MDR tools and
Familiar with Windows firewall concepts, including rule
Excellent written and verbal communication
